caption: Very quaint atmosphere food was really good, service was very good not great but we are in a pandemic so I'm sure there strapped for time and short staffed but I definitely recommend you stop here especially if your in the area!!!! Will revisit soon.

When you looking for a delicious vegan meal, LuAnne's Wild Ginger is the right place to go for you!  They have an amazing variety of dishes which you can choose from I decided to have the dumplings as a start. They were a great taste.  For the entree I choose the House Bi-Bimbap. I have just one word for it.... AMAZING!!!! They have the right amount of each ingredient, combined with a great multigrain rice.  Even I was full and satisfied, I couldn't resist and try the chocolate cake. It is delicious and a huge portion. I had to take it home which allowed me to enjoy it another day.  The current outdoor setup is great. They have separated places for each party (up to 4 people).  You should check this place out, when you have the chance!
Favorite restaurant ever!!!!

I have been patronizing this restaurant for years.  Love love love the food.  Service always amazing.  Food is fresh & delish.  One of my fav vegetarian restaurants overall.

Ordered the eggplant green beans and the curry stew. Food was mediocre, curry was ok. The eggplant was waaay too sweet, I was thinking how much sugar was in the dish while I was eating. I hope it was a mistake by the chef, otherwise should really consider adding less sugar.

I feel like the dishes here lack flavor, maybe that means they are healthy. The options are fairly standard for an asian fusion veg place. This place usually isn't my first choice but I appreciate having an all veg restaurant in the neighborhood as backup.

The food here tastes excellent, there's no denying it. It is not surprising that they have 3 locations currently open. The general tsoy chicken is super yummy garlicky deliciousness. The vibe is nice and the seating is comfortable. Only complaint about this place is that some of the prices don't seem reasonable. $12 for a kale salad seems a little obscene even by NYC standards. I would definitely come back.

Came here on a lunch outing with my coworkers. Clean and open space inside and I think there's an outdoor space (too cold for that right now). We shared appetizers: dumplings, edamame, tofu, and veggie wraps. They were okay, nothing spectacular. I got the Malaysian curry lunch special and a mango lassi. My drink was probably the best part of the meal. If this is my introduction to veganism, I don't think I'll convert. Everything was on the mild side and nothing stood out. The menu also seemed all over the place? Chinese, Japanese, Indian, etc. However, service was efficient and my coworkers seemed to love their dishes.
This is one of my fav vegan restaurants near down town Brooklyn. The general tsao is a must try. The waiters are nice and the service is A+. They also deliver! I am really happy to find a place this.

My husband and I can't get enough of this place! We have been to the restaurant and have also ordered takeout a few times - we have not had any other takeout since discovering LuAnnes! We have tried the Malaysian Curry stew, satay tempeh and also the crispy soy protein. The curry is awesome - the soy is sliced thin and has a nice texture and taste, the veg is very fresh - overall it feels like a very clean healthy dish, not oily or too heavy. The tempeh is great also - whatever way they have marinaded it genuinely makes it the best tempeh I have had! The crispy soy protein is lightly breaded and fried, however again it's more like a light fry rather than super greasy. Nice dipping sauces to accompany this dish. If you visit the restaurant it's a lovely experience also, friendly staff, nice ambiance. Delivery is generally super quick and the food has always arrived hot. 5 stars all around, reasonably priced also!
Very pleasant atmosphere and customer service. In addition, the food was very good!
Consistency is everything and over the past few years nothing has changed, taste-wise. Always a delicious meal.

I had the most wonderful time here with friends for dinner on a Saturday night!! We ordered some huge Sapporos, curry samosas, soy cutlet platter, fisherman's veggie platter (soyseafood), and the mango soy protein dish! All dishes were served with brown rice and we finished EVERYTHING. The portions were generous, the vegetables were well done, and all of the meat alternatives were great copycats. Come here hungry and leave with a full, but not heavy, belly! Recommend for vegans and those adjacent to vegans and everyone in between!
Great food, great service, great ambiance!
Great food and great ambiance. Good tea selection with caffein ratings on the menu! And they dont rush you out. Love it here!

This place is great for all vegan food. I think you have to be a bit smart and what you order, maybe avoid typical Thai food where you have very specific expectations. For example, they had the worst pad Thai I've ever eaten, even frozen pad Thai is better. It was dry with not enough sauce, didn't really have anything but the noodles ... You have the option to make it spicy! But spicy is suuuuuper spicy so maybe go for medium spicy if you don't enjoy 🔥🔥🔥. Vegan peanut butter and chocolate cake is dry and decadent, we mostly ate the mousse out of it. The kimchi pancakes and seitan was perfect.

The atmosphere, and music, we're all so wonderful as usual. The service, was not so good. When we sat down, we waited a long time for them to take our order. I asked for another drink, and after 10 minutes still hadn't gotten until I asked again for it. My daughter thought they were a bit condescending too. After our brief visit to Ikea an unplanned search for vegetarian food led us to this place, also called Lu Anne's Wild Ginger. Inside decor and ambience was very pleasant and comforting. We loved their starters especially the Seitan Skewers - tender Seitans  dipped in savory satay sauce and Stuffed Wontons served with delicious mango dip. For entrée we had Malaysian Curry Stew and Jap-Chae korean-style stir-fried sweet potato noodles. Curry significantly lacked the coconut flavor as opposed to claims on menu card and was very bland and flat in taste but the noodles was very tasteful. Overall it was a very good experience to explore from countles vegan varieties and will definitely visit the place again.
Place isn't bad and service is at its reasonable paste  but it's too overpriced considering that everything  is made out of soy.

This was one of the best meals I've ever eaten. Had general tso seitan - still craving it. Wish I lived in Brooklyn so I could go here every week (or day). We all shared our food and everything was amazing- pad Thai, pad see ew, and some other thing. Anyway- can't go wrong. Everything is awesome.

Skeptics of vegan/vegetarian spots should eat here!  I held out for a long time to try a vegetarian spot and this place delivers.  I had the Kale Avocado Rice Bowl with tofu and it was an eye opening dish.  My girlfriend had the pad Thai which was equally delicious!  We will definitely be back!
Amazing food. I went on a date night with my Vegan Girlfriend & she was highly impressed. The atmosphere is pleasant as well. A good time all around & friendly wait staff. Definitely going back.
Delicious Food! Visited for the first time today. I tried the Satay Tempeh, which was unbelievable. Also the pumpkin soup has a light texture and is tasty. Staff is courteous and attentive.
Delicious pad Thai,  very courteous staff.
Basil soy protein is amazing, one of the best vegan dishes I have eatin

I must have been delusional the night in February I had dinner here.  This is a popular, well-reviewed restaurant and my dining companions were very happy with their meals.  I thought everything was slightly off, from the attitude of our waiter, to the temperature, flavor profile,  care of preparation, and presentation of the food served.
Best hot and sour soup in NYC. Not a fan of the other dishes I have had...
enjoyable restaurant with good service and great food.  You wouldn't realize it's veg.

Don't let the vegan label fool you if you're a meat eater, it tastes just as good as the real thing. The General Tsao's soy protein has the texture and taste of chicken. There are non-vegan options for dessert like gelatto.
A delightful vegan paradise~ Delicious food with none of the cruelty & twice the flavor!
